post.body: HAPPY BIRTHDAY, BECCA!!!
This' the dog picture I was telling you about: http://tinyurl.com/5mjwvz
Which live set are you watching/listening to?
not your best work. NEXT!
Andrew WK in the morning? Why not?
Nothing like looking at old pictures for a good laugh.
Sara (of Tegan & Sara) listed Fucked Up's "The Chemistry…" as her 4th favorite album of 2008. This gives me all the reason to lover her more
New video interview w/Trent Reznor: http://tinyurl.com/6kv82c
I never understand why my sound settings always get out of center.
It's nice going home from school & the sun is still out.
A dude just got denied a goodbye hug from my astro lab teacher.
Finished my socio final in 35 minutes. Now off to cram for astro final.
My Socio professor has been late to class every day this entire semester. It's 10am, the final's supposed to start now & he's not here. Ha!!
I watched a movie in my Socio class about marijuana, & there's audio clip in it that Tiger Uppercut! sampled.
Joke answer on study guide: "typical signs of Yakuza are: body piercings & silk suits, full body tats, or italian suits & a small penis."
Just saw the footage of Bush getting shoes chucked at him. Did not think I'd laugh that hard.
'90s dance n' R&B play list complete!
As I read through my notes I'm discovering horrible type-os, such as "nipple" got fucked up and written as "nipeoplee."
an **
Taking a break from studying to make a Azn-as-fuck '90s R&B play list. Wutz up, LMNTary skew.
All I heard walking passed a TV showing UFC was, "…Shot to Ortiz's Liver! A tribute to Bas Ruten…" Dang-a—d-dang-a—d-dang…
Fake Arnold rules
Guess this song: "Fuck you, fuck you, fuck yeow!!!"
I remember why I haven't watched this movie for so long. What a weird/depressing movie.
Watching Suicide Club for the 2nd time since I bought it 2 years ago.
Scratched the silver coating off the back of my iTunes gift card too hard. Now I can't make out the 2nd n' 3rd characters.
4:30 AM and I'm brainstorming ways to purchase a pair of shoes w/o feeling like I'm wasting money.
Benjamin Button: great, great movie; being stood up by a friend: not so great.
So many people at the movies. Don't you assholes have families to spend Christmas with?
Playing a show in a full suit seems badass.
Finished opening X-mas gifts; now watching my live Morrissey DVD.
And I have a stomach ache. Fvck… Nothing a little T-2: Judgment Day can't fix.
Uploading pictures to the internetz always fucks my shit up.
I'm finally discovering who shot all these photos I've liked over the years: Ryan Russell.
Whoa. Discovering an unreleased (good quality) live recording of a NIN song called "Not So Pretty Now." I can hear this during a car chase.
I got accepted into the follow-up design class this spring; however, I was warned to better my problem solving and form giving skills. Fuck.
Wish I could've stolen every Christmas gift I bought.
Haha—The guy that played Shang Tseung in the MK movie, also in the last Asian themed movie I watched, appears again in this movie.
I must be on some Asian themed movie craze—third day, third Asian movie: Memoirs Of A Geisha.
Every time I read Zooey Deschanel's name I see it as "Zoey Disney Channel."
